A woman in her thirties was killed in an accident on the R103 between Balgowan and Nottingham Road in the KwaZulu-Natal Midlands on Monday afternoon. Roland Robertson of the Midlands EMS said on arrival paramedics noticed two cars with extensive damage. He said one person was entrapped inside one of the cars. “She sadly showed no signs of life and was declared deceased on scene. A second person from the car sustained critical injuries and required urgent advanced life support intervention. She was transported to the hospital,” said Robertson. He said earlier on Monday, there was another accident on the R103 near Lions River. “A family of four sustained injuries ranging from moderate to serious,” Robertson said.